---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Section from "../../../components/common/Section.astro";
import Prose from "../../../components/Prose.astro";
import { GLOBAL } from "../../../lib/variables";

const title = "CleanTube — Privacy Policy";
const url = `${GLOBAL.rootUrl}/apps/cleantube/privacy`;
---

<Layout>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <title>{title} • {GLOBAL.username}</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Privacy policy for CleanTube, a Safari browser extension for macOS that removes distracting elements from YouTube." />
    <meta property="og:title" content={`${title} • ${GLOBAL.username}`} />
    <meta property="og:description" content="CleanTube is designed to work entirely on your device. It does not collect, transmit, sell, or share any personal data." />
    <meta property="og:url" content={url} />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content={`${title} • ${GLOBAL.username}`} />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content="CleanTube is designed to work entirely on your device. It does not collect, transmit, sell, or share any personal data." />
    <meta http-equiv="content-language" content="en" />
    <meta name="language" content="English" />
    <link rel="canonical" href={url} />
  </Fragment>
  <Section class="mt-8 mb-16">
    <Prose>
      <h1>CleanTube — Privacy Policy</h1>

      <p><strong>Effective date:</strong> 2026-04-21<br /><strong>Last updated:</strong> 2026-04-21</p>

      <p>
        CleanTube ("the app", "we", "our") is a Safari browser extension for macOS that modifies the
        appearance of YouTube web pages to remove Shorts, recommended videos, the Home tab, and
        related distracting elements, and to redirect the YouTube home page to the Subscriptions feed.
      </p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains what information the app does and does not handle.
        <strong>CleanTube is designed to work entirely on your device. It does not collect,
        transmit, sell, or share any personal data.</strong>
      </p>

      <hr />

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

      <p><strong>None.</strong></p>

      <p>
        CleanTube does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. It has no servers, no
        accounts, and no backend. Your preference settings are saved locally on your device only and
        never leave it. Uninstalling the app removes them.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Third-Party Services</h2>

      <p>
        CleanTube does <strong>not</strong> integrate with, send data to, or load code from any
        third-party analytics, advertising, crash reporting, A/B testing, or tracking services.
        There are no third-party SDKs in the app.
      </p>

      <p>
        Note: YouTube itself is operated by Google and has its own privacy practices. When you use
        YouTube in your browser, Google's Privacy Policy applies to that use, independent of
        CleanTube. CleanTube has no affiliation with, and is not endorsed by, YouTube or Google LLC.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Children's Privacy</h2>

      <p>
        CleanTube does not knowingly collect any information from anyone, including children under 13.
        Because the app collects no personal data at all, it complies with the U.S. Children's Online
        Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) by design.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Data Retention and Deletion</h2>

      <p>
        Because we do not collect or transmit any data, there is nothing for us to retain or delete
        on any server. Locally stored preference toggles remain on your device until you:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Change them in the extension's popup or the companion macOS app, or</li>
        <li>Uninstall the CleanTube extension / app, or</li>
        <li>Clear Safari's extension data for CleanTube.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Your Rights (GDPR / CCPA)</h2>

      <p>
        Because CleanTube does not collect or process personal data, there is no personal data for us
        to access, correct, export, or delete on your behalf. You retain full control of your local
        preferences on your own device at all times.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Security</h2>

      <p>
        All preference data is stored locally on your Mac using the standard storage mechanisms
        provided by Safari and macOS. We do not operate any servers, so there is no remote database
        that could be breached.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>

      <p>
        If this policy is ever updated, the new version will be posted at the same URL with a revised
        "Last updated" date. Material changes will be highlighted at the top of the page. Continued
        use of CleanTube after an update constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Contact</h2>

      <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or CleanTube's privacy practices, contact:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Developer:</strong> Santiago Rhenals</li>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> santiago@srhenals.com</li>
        <li><strong>App:</strong> CleanTube for Safari (macOS)</li>
      </ul>
    </Prose>
  </Section>
</Layout>
